<BYLINE>By LAWRENCE L. KNUTSON</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The Senate Foreign Relations Committee postponed action on three of President <PERSON> Bush </PERSON>'s ambassadorial nominees Tuesday after Democrats complained their only visible qualifications are large <ORGANIZATION> GOP </ORGANIZATION> contributions. Sen. <PERSON> Paul </PERSON> <PERSON> Sarbanes </PERSON>, D-Md., initiated the delay when he complained that <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> ambassadors should have at least some qualifications for the job The <ORGANIZATION> Senate </ORGANIZATION> is set to close down for the Independence Day recess, so <PERSON> Sarbanes </PERSON>' request for a one-week delay effectively stops until mid July at the earliest any action on the nominations to fill ambassadorships in <LOCATION> Spain </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Australia </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Zealand </LOCATION>. `` In the past we've had to hold our noses'' and let similar nominees with political connections go through, <PERSON> Sarbanes </PERSON> said. `` But eventually someone ought to say stop.'' `` If it's going to be a bidding war ... at least we should put it up for public bids so the money goes to the <ORGANIZATION> U.S. </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Treasury </ORGANIZATION>,'' <PERSON> Sarbanes </PERSON> said. <PERSON> Sarbanes </PERSON> targeted three. They are: _ <PERSON> Joseph </PERSON> <PERSON> Zappala </PERSON>, a <LOCATION> Florida </LOCATION> land developer and national co-chairman of <PERSON> Bush </PERSON>'s fund raising committee who has been nominated to be <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> ambassador to <LOCATION> Spain </LOCATION> <PERSON> Sarbanes </PERSON> said he contributed $ 126,000 to the <PERSON> Bush </PERSON> campaign. _ <PERSON> Marvin </PERSON> <PERSON> Sembler </PERSON>, a <LOCATION> Florida </LOCATION> shopping center tycoon who has been named to be ambassador to <LOCATION> Australia </LOCATION> <PERSON> Sarbanes </PERSON> said <PERSON> Sembler </PERSON> was a $ 127,000 <PERSON> Bush </PERSON> contributor. _ <PERS