<HEAD>Defense Ministry Says Romania Builds Border Wire Fence</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BUDAPEST, Hungary (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The government says <LOCATION> Romania </LOCATION> has nearly completed construction of a 6-foot barbed wire fence along its border with <LOCATION> Hungary </LOCATION>, but cast doubt on a foreign press report that a brick wall is being built. The Times of <LOCATION> London </LOCATION> on Monday reported that <LOCATION> Bucharest </LOCATION> is building a wall along its border with <LOCATION> Hungary </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Yugoslavia </LOCATION> to prevent defections. <LOCATION> Hungary </LOCATION>'s official <ORGANIZATION> MTI </ORGANIZATION> news agency said Tuesday that its border guards had reported `` no signs of wall construction.'' `` Nevertheless, a 2 -LCB- - meter wire fence is being set up on the Romanian side of the border ... which has been completed along 90 percent of the border length,'' the agency said `` Since it appears to be an ordinary wire fence, the -LRB- Hungarian -RRB- border guards suppose that no electricity will be led into it,'' the agency said. It added that the fence is about 80 feet inside Romanian territory. `` The latest works indicate that ditches have been dug on both sides of the fence to prevent breakthroughs by cars,'' <ORGANIZATION> MTI </ORGANIZATION> said. <LOCATION> Romania </LOCATION>'s border with <LOCATION> Hungary </LOCATION> extends 275 miles. An estimated 30,000 Romanians, most of them ethnic Hungarians, have fled to <LOCATION> Hungary </LOCATION> in the past few years seeking refuge from chronic hardships under the regime of President <PERSON> Nicolae </PERSON> <PERSON> Ceausescu </PERSON>. Ethnic Hungarians also claim discriminatory policies toward minorities in <LOCATION> Romania </LOCATION>. During the first five months of this year, 3,231 Romanians crossed ilegally into <LOCATION> Hungary </LOCATION>, deputy Interior Minister <PERSON> Zoltan </PERSON> <PERSON> Gal </PERSON> said last week. He said the Cabinet would soon discuss plans to open three refugees camps in eastern <LOCATION> Hungary </LOCATION> to co