<SECOND>PM-A Painting's Value,0298</SECOND>
<HEAD>Canvas that Cost $8 in 1956 Sells for $150,000</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A 19th-century painting set in ancient <LOCATION> Rome </LOCATION> of a young woman about to bathe has been sold at auction for $ 153,450 _ nearly 20,000 times its 1956 purchase price of $ 8. `` It certainly does reflect an extraordinary change in taste, but that is n't unique in art,'' said <PERSON> Sotheby </PERSON>'s <PERSON> Simon </PERSON> <PERSON> Taylor </PERSON> after the sale Tuesday of `` Diadumene'' by Sir <PERSON> Edward </PERSON> <PERSON> Poynter </PERSON>. The auction house had expected more because of the vogue for once-neglected Victorian works. It had estimated the painting would fetch up to $ 232,500. <PERSON> Poynter </PERSON>, in 1885, had painted the young woman nude but he added diaphanous drapery after it was exhibited at the <ORGANIZATION> Royal </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Academy </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Arts </ORGANIZATION> and provoked letters from shocked viewers. One letter to the press, signed `` British Matron,'' said the writer had barred her daughters from going to the the exhibition. Another letter said the painting would produce a `` burning sense of shame'' in any `` modest woman on the arm of father, brother or lover.'' <PERSON> Poynter </PERSON> was known for such paintings but his most famous work, reproduced in the tens of thousands in its day, was `` Faithful unto Death.'' It depicted a Roman sentry staying at his post during the destruction of <LOCATION> Pompeii </LOCATION> by the Vesuvius volcano. The seller and buyer of `` Diadumene'' were not identified. The painting had been auctioned in 1956 at a sale of the contents of <LOCATION> Ashley </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Manor </LOCATION>, owned by <PERSON> Lady </PERSON> <PERSON> Agnes </PERSON> <PERSON> Chichester </PERSON> <PERSON> Dixon-Hartland </PERSON>. Top price at Tuesday's auction of 19th century European art was $ 2.3 million _ more than double the estimate _ paid anonymously for `` Grandfather's Birthday,'' a family fireside scene by Austrian artist <PERSON> Ferdinand </PERSON> <PERSON> Georg </PERSON> <PERSON> Waldmueller </PERSON>. It was a record for his work.
