. `` I recognize how difficult it is for some senators to state the conclusion most of us share: Mr. <PERSON> Gregg </PERSON> has not been straight with us,'' <PERSON> Cranston </PERSON> said. `` The implications for Mr. <PERSON> Gregg </PERSON> _ and for the president _ are not pleasant.'' The panel also postponed action on three other nominations after Democrats complained that the nominees' only visible qualifications were large <ORGANIZATION> GOP </ORGANIZATION> contributions. Sen. <PERSON> Paul </PERSON> <PERSON> Sarbanes </PERSON>, D-Md., initiated the delay when he complained that <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> ambassadors should have at least some qualifications The three include:
