<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>PARCHMAN, Miss. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A black man who insisted he was unjustly convicted by an all-white jury was executed in the gas chamber early today for a five-day robbery spree in which three people were slain. <PERSON> Leo </PERSON> <PERSON> Edwards </PERSON> <PERSON> Jr. </PERSON>, 36, of <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Orleans </LOCATION>, appeared to gasp for breath and shrug his shoulders several times as the cyanide gas swirled around him. He was declared dead at 12:15 a.m., minutes after being strapped into a chair in the gas chamber. <PERSON> Edwards </PERSON> was the fourth person executed at the state penitentiary at <LOCATION> Parchman </LOCATION> and the 113th in the nation since the <ORGANIZATION> U.S. </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Supreme </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Court </ORGANIZATION> reinstated the death penalty in 1976. <PERSON> Edwards </PERSON> was executed for the June 14, 1980, shooting death of <PERSON> Jackson </PERSON> convenience store clerk <PERSON> Linzy </PERSON> <PERSON> Don </PERSON> <PERSON> Dixon </PERSON>. The robbery netted $ 111 and came during a spree in Hinds and <LOCATION> Madison </LOCATION> counties in which two other people were killed and two were wounded. Also participating in the spree was <PERSON> Mike </PERSON> <PERSON> White </PERSON>, who escaped with <PERSON> Edwards </PERSON> from the <ORGANIZATION> Louisiana </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> State </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Penitentiary </ORGANIZATION> at <LOCATION> Angola </LOCATION>. White is serving two life terms after pleading guilty to murder in the death of <PERSON> Dixon </PERSON> and a bar owner. Defense attorneys protested that prosecutors deliberately excluded blacks from the jury, denying <PERSON> Edwards </PERSON> a fair trial. On Tuesday, the <ORGANIZATION> U.S. </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Supreme </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Court </ORGANIZATION> voted 7-2 against a stay, and Gov. <PERSON> Ray </PERSON> <PERSON> Mabus </PERSON> rejected <PERSON> Edwards </PERSON>'