 There is change afoot in this country, politically and militarily,'' <PERSON> Crow </PERSON> said today, adding that he found <PERSON> Gorbachev </PERSON> `` very impressive.'' <PERSON> Crowe </PERSON> said <PERSON> Gorbachev </PERSON>'s plan to withdraw 500 tactical nuclear weapons from <LOCATION> Eastern </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Europe </LOCATION> and President <PERSON> Bush </PERSON>'s proposals on reducing conventional forces made him optimistic about superpower arms talks. `` We now believe there are some positive offers, some constructive offers on the table, that both sides are serious and sincere and that we can now continue the process of negotiations and some optimism,'' <PERSON> Crowe </PERSON> said. But he said that it is dangerous for arms control negotiators to be rushed by a desire on both sides for disarmament.
