 We can definitely take this path,'' he said. In the past, settlers doing army reserve duty were barred from serving near their hometowns. Most Israeli men serve in the reserves for up to two months a year until age 54. <PERSON> Shamir </PERSON> also criticized an attack Tuesday in which a 23-year-old Jewish settler fired at a group of Palestinians standing at an intersection near <LOCATION> Tel </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Aviv </LOCATION>. Two Arabs were wounded, one of them seriously. <LOCATION> Israel </LOCATION> radio said the assailant, who staged the shooting after attending the funeral of the slain settler, has a police record. `` We must prevent such actions. They only strengthen the other side, the extremists among the Arabs,'' <PERSON> Shamir </PERSON> said.
