taken that step of asking for an investigation,'' <PERSON> Walker </PERSON> said. `` I think it's an appropriate kind of step to suggest that the other caucus ought to also be willing to do the kind of tough thing that is involved in what our conference did today.'' The document notes that <ORGANIZATION> House </ORGANIZATION> members, `` in order to perform their constitutional duties, must conduct themselves with integrity'' and that <ORGANIZATION> House </ORGANIZATION> rules require conduct which will not bring disrepute on the institution. <ORGANIZATION> Lukens </ORGANIZATION>, 58 and divorced, has said he planned to fight the conviction and remain in <ORGANIZATION> Congress </ORGANIZATION> in the meantime. `` I refuse to allow the lies and deceit of one delinquent individual to ruin me. I am now fighting for my life,'' he said in a statement following his conviction. <ORGANIZATION> Lukens </ORGANIZATION> said in that statement that his accuser had `` fantasies of ` getting even with the establishment.''' But the court refused to allow him to bring up evidence he wanted to present to raise doubts about her reliability, the conservative lawmaker said. Since the conviction, <LOCATION> Ohio </LOCATION> state <ORGANIZATION> GOP </ORGANIZATION> chairman <PERSON> Robert </PERSON> <PERSON> Bennett </PERSON> has said <ORGANIZATION> Lukens </ORGANIZATION> will not be on the party's ticket in 1990 based on opposition from local party officials. <ORGANIZATION> Lukens </ORGANIZATION>' <ORGANIZATION> Republican </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> House </ORGANIZATION> colleagues also have distanced themselves from him. His conviction has harmed their cause at a time when they have been seeking to use the ethics issue against Democrats. <ORGANIZATION> Lukens </ORGANIZATION> is currently in the second term of his second stint in <ORGANIZATION> Congress </ORGANIZATION>. He also was in <ORGANIZATION> Congress </ORGANIZATION> for two terms from 1967 to 1971.
