<HEAD>`Girl Vigilantes' Project Pro-Choice Message on Building</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ATLANTA (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A guerrilla abortion-rights group projected a 100-foot image of a naked woman on a downtown building, the word `` Mine'' scrawled across her body. The image stayed there for an hour Monday night, drawing spectators and slowing traffic nearby. `` The statement is being made as we await the <ORGANIZATION> Supreme </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Court </ORGANIZATION> decision re-evaluating <PERSON> Roe </PERSON> v. <PERSON> Wade </PERSON>,'' the secretive group said, referring to the case that legalized abortions, in a message sent to facsimile machines. They called the giant nude `` a monumental visual statement affirming every woman's right to say ` My Body Is Mine.''' Their fax messages end with the statement: `` Girl Vigilantes. We Draw The Line.'' <LOCATION> Atlanta </LOCATION> was the scene of major anti-abortion protests during the Democratic National Convention last summer.
