ng gifts. Parliament Speaker <PERSON> Yannis </PERSON> <PERSON> Alevras </PERSON> said the evidence against the two ministers would be kept secret until its presentation to the first session of the new <ORGANIZATION> Parliament </ORGANIZATION>, scheduled for July 3. Consultations to form a coalition government are expected to continue until next week. Each of the three party leaders is given given three days to try to accomplish this, with <PERSON> Mistotakis </PERSON> having the first go.
