 has been fed by wind and dry grass. `` If things work like they're working now, I'd say two to three days,'' information officer <PERSON> Sam </PERSON> <PERSON> Logan </PERSON> said Tuesday. `` If all of a sudden it dries up and we get some crazy winds, it could do something else.'' The area is so dry that alligators have abandoned secluded marshes in the <ORGANIZATION> Arthur </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> R. </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Marshall </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Loxahatchee </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Wildlife </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Refuge </ORGANIZATION>, <LOCATION> Florida </LOCATION>'s largest, for a canal on its rim. As a result, the refuge has been closed to boaters and fishermen. In <LOCATION> California </LOCATION>, a 175-acre brush fire in the hills above <LOCATION> San </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Clemente </LOCATION> was contained at 8 a.m., and firefighters earlier doused a 300-acre blaze in the <LOCATION> Newbury </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Park </LOCATION> area of <LOCATION> Ventura </LOCATION> <LOCATION> County </LOCATION> and a 115-acre fire in <LOCATION> San </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Bernardino </LOCATION> <LOCATION> County </LOCATION>'s <LOCATION> Devore </LOCATION> area.
