reventing a loan for irrigation from being properly spent, for example, we would not want to keep putting out the money,'' <PERSON> Vogl </PERSON> said in an interview. The bank lends $ 2 billion to $ 2.5 billion a year to <LOCATION> China </LOCATION>, the third-largest borrower after <LOCATION> India </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Mexico </LOCATION>. Pastor <PERSON> Sison </PERSON>, spokesman on <LOCATION> Asia </LOCATION>, calculated that $ 780 million worth of new lending for <LOCATION> China </LOCATION> was due for approval by the board before the bank's fiscal year ends June 30. The bank is planning to lend $ 20 billion to $ 21 billion this year to over 100 Third World countries. The usual rush is on to complete this program by the end of the fiscal year and the board has scheduled three meetings next week. <PERSON> Sison </PERSON> said it would be hard to transfer to other borrowers the amounts designated for <LOCATION> China </LOCATION>. A spokesman at the <ORGANIZATION> International </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Monetary </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Fund </ORGANIZATION>, the bank's sister organization, said it has no loans pending or being disbursed to <LOCATION> China </LOCATION>. <LOCATION> China </LOCATION> does get loans from the <ORGANIZATION> Asian </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Development </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Bank </ORGANIZATION>, an international body with headquarters in <LOCATION> Manila </LOCATION>.
