<HEAD>Israeli Warplanes Hit Palestinian Base; Kill 1, Wound 6</HEAD>
<HEAD>LaserPhotos BEI2,3</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By RIAD KAHWAJI</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Ppress Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>NAAMEH, Lebanon (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Israeli warplanes destroyed the headquarters of a dissident Palestinian guerrilla faction Wednesday, and the guerrillas reported one fighter killed and six wounded. Palls of dust and smoke billowed from the oak woods around <LOCATION> Naameh </LOCATION>, 10 miles south of <LOCATION> Beirut </LOCATION>, as guerrillas opened up with anti-aircraft guns on fighter-bombers that dived from clear skies. The jets released scarlet balloons to deflect heat-seeking missiles. Guerrillas launched one SA-7, but the Soviet-made projectile missed its target. Police said four warplanes struck two positions of the Popular Front for the <ORGANIZATION> Liberation </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Palestine-General </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Command </ORGANIZATION> in the bluffs of <LOCATION> Naameh </LOCATION>. A police spokesman said eight guerrillas were wounded. A statement from the guerrillas' headquarters in <LOCATION> Damascus </LOCATION> reported one guerrilla killed and six wounded. It said the raid lasted 105 minutes, during which nine formations of U.S.-built F-4 Phantom and Skyhawk bombers dropped more than 100 rockets. The statement said guerrillas prevented several attempts to land airborne and seaborne commandos in the area, where they maintain bases in a chain of tunnels across the <LOCATION> Naameh </LOCATION> hills. Israeli gunboats were cruising the <LOCATION> Mediterranean </LOCATION> and two helicopter gunships hovered over the beaches, but reporters saw no attempt to land troops. In <LOCATION> Jerusalem </LOCATION>, the Israeli army said its planes returned safely from an attack on targets that `` served as the headquarters for <PERSON> Ahmed </PERSON> <PERSON> Jibril </PERSON>.'' It was the third air raid on <LOCATION> Lebanon </LOCATION> this week and the ninth this year. On Friday, <LOCATION> Israeli </LOCATION> warplanes bombed south <LOCATION> Lebanon </LOCATION>'s <LOCATION> Rashidiyeh </LOCATION> refugee camp, wounding two