<HEAD>Black Priest to Start Own African-American Catholic Congregation</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By ANITA WOMACK</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A black priest who plans to start a separate African-American Catholic congregation said Wednesday he is not defying <ORGANIZATION> Roman </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Catholic </ORGANIZATION> tenets, despite warnings from church leaders. `` While the establishment of this congregation does not enjoy the endorsement or authority of His Eminence, <PERSON> James </PERSON> <PERSON> Cardinal </PERSON> <PERSON> Hickey </PERSON>, we see ourselves as being obedient to the law of God and following the dictates of our consciences,'' said the Rev. <PERSON> George </PERSON> <PERSON> A. </PERSON> <PERSON> Stallings </PERSON> <PERSON> Jr. </PERSON>. <PERSON> Stallings </PERSON>, 41, said he plans to create the <ORGANIZATION> Imani </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Temple </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> African-American </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Catholic </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Congregation </ORGANIZATION> in <LOCATION> Washington </LOCATION> because the <ORGANIZATION> Roman </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Catholic </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Church </ORGANIZATION> has failed to meet the spiritual and cultural demands of its black parishioners However, the priest said his move is not intended to be a departure from Catholicism. He said his church would adopt a Zairian liturgy and would combine readings from the works of noted black writers and philosophers, such as <PERSON> Martin </PERSON> <PERSON> Luther </PERSON> <PERSON> King </PERSON> <PERSON> Jr. </PERSON> and <PERSON> Malcolm </PERSON> <PERSON> X </PERSON>, with traditional Scripture passages. <PERSON> Imani </PERSON> means `` faith'' in <LOCATION> Swahili </LOCATION>. Cardinal <PERSON> Hickey </PERSON> of <LOCATION> Washington </LOCATION> and a prominent black church leader both condemned <PERSON> Stallings </PERSON>' actions. `` In spite of his claims to the contrary, <PERSON> Father </PERSON> <PERSON> Stallings </PERSON>' action is a serious step towards separating himself from the <ORGANIZATION> Roman </ORG