<BYLINE>By JOHN WRIGHT</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>MEXICO CITY (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A former federal security agent and onetime movie actor said Wednesday he was part of a team that killed newspaper columnist <PERSON> Manuel </PERSON> <PERSON> Buendia </PERSON> in 1984, but he maintained he does not know who ordered the killing. The <LOCATION> Mexico </LOCATION> <LOCATION> City </LOCATION> attorney general's office had police arrest ex-agent <PERSON> Juan </PERSON> <PERSON> Rafael </PERSON> <PERSON> Mora </PERSON> <PERSON> Avila </PERSON> on Tuesday and produced him at a news conference the next day. <PERSON> Mora </PERSON> said he was in a squad that killed <PERSON> Buendia </PERSON>, but said he did not know what the operation was about. `` I'm a career policeman, not a criminal nor a killer,'' <PERSON> Mora </PERSON>, 36, a member of a prominent political family, told reporters. He said the triggerman was a police informer named <PERSON> Jose </PERSON> <PERSON> Luis </PERSON> <PERSON> Ochoa </PERSON> <PERSON> Alonso </PERSON>, nicknamed `` El Chocorrol'' _ a type of chocolate _ because of his dark complexion. He said the man died two months ago. <PERSON> Buendia </PERSON>, whose front-page column in the newspaper Excelsior exposed wrongdoing in high places, was fatally shot May 30, 1984, at the entrance of a parking garage near his office. <PERSON> Mora </PERSON> said he, <PERSON> Ochoa </PERSON> and a police officer met at the now-dissolved <ORGANIZATION> Federal </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Security </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Administration </ORGANIZATION>, similar to the <ORGANIZATION> FBI </ORGANIZATION>, the afternoon <PERSON> Buendia </PERSON> was killed, and set out on motorcycles on a secret operation to silence a troublemaker. He said he remembered hearing shots but did not witness the killing. `` I did n't know what was happening,'' <PERSON> Mora </PERSON> told reporters. Assistant Attorney General <PERSON> Abraham </PERSON> <PERSON> Polo </PERSON> <PERSON> Uzcanga </PERSON> quoted <PERSON> Mora </PERSON> as saying that after th