<PERSON> Bennett </PERSON> has said he will not be on the party's ticket in 1990, and the senior member of the state's <ORGANIZATION> GOP </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> House </ORGANIZATION> delegation, Rep. <PERSON> Chalmers </PERSON> <PERSON> Wylie </PERSON>, has said <ORGANIZATION> Lukens </ORGANIZATION> `` should do the gentlemanly thing and resign.'' <ORGANIZATION> Lukens </ORGANIZATION> has vowed to fight, and his spokesman said Wednesday's action was welcome because an ethics probe could `` once and for all bring forth the truth about this entire episode. The spokesman, <PERSON> William </PERSON> <PERSON> Jarrell </PERSON>, said <ORGANIZATION> Lukens </ORGANIZATION> was hampered in court because he was not permitted to cast doubt on the motives and credibility of the girl and her mother, who were <ORGANIZATION> Lukens </ORGANIZATION>' accusers. `` Now we'll be able to bring forth the background and the motives,'' he said. Meanwhile, <ORGANIZATION> Lukens </ORGANIZATION> learned Wednesday that a polyp removed from his colon was benign. Spokesman <PERSON> Jarrell </PERSON> said <ORGANIZATION> Lukens </ORGANIZATION> was in good health and the throat cancer diagnosed in 1984 remains in remission. In presenting the Republican resolution, <PERSON> Michel </PERSON> said it was unprecedented for the conference to call for an ethics probe of one of its own members. The document asks the ethics panel to `` determine whether Rep. <PERSON> Donald </PERSON> <PERSON> E. </PERSON> `` Buz'' <ORGANIZATION> Lukens </ORGANIZATION> failed to conduct himself at all times in a manner which reflects creditably on the House of Representatives.'' It notes that <ORGANIZATION> House </ORGANIZATION> members, `` in order to perform their constitutional duties, must conduct themselves with integrity'' and that <ORGANIZATION> House </ORGANIZATION> rules require conduct which will not bring disrepute on the institution. <PERSON> Michel </PERSON> said the <ORGANIZATION> GOP </ORGANIZATION> w