<HEAD>Pete Kowanko Stars as Man of Future in `Gifted One'</HEAD>
<HEAD>LaserPhoto LA1 of June 20</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By JERRY BUCK</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>AP Television Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <PERSON> Pete </PERSON> <PERSON> Kowanko </PERSON> plays the latest in a long line of television heroes on the run in his role as the title character in the <ORGANIZATION> NBC </ORGANIZATION> Sunday movie `` The Gifted One.'' Kowanko plays <PERSON> Michael </PERSON> <PERSON> Grant </PERSON>, a man of special mystical powers, pursued by Dr. <PERSON> Boardman </PERSON> -LRB- <PERSON> John </PERSON> <PERSON> Rhys-Davies </PERSON> -RRB-, an opportunistic scientist who can hardly wait to experiment on <PERSON> Grant </PERSON> to see what makes him tick. `` <PERSON> Michael </PERSON> <PERSON> Grant </PERSON>'s mind uses the full potential that man's capable of,'' said <PERSON> Kowanko </PERSON>. `` He's gifted. He can direct the electrical power of his body like a laser to heal. He can place himself in synch with any living thing or lock into someone else's subconscious. `` That gift can also be painful. He has an acute sense of right and wrong. He does n't want to take advantage of it in a dark way. Nor does he want to be exploited by the military or anyone else.'' The `` chase'' story is a favorite television premise. The most popular was `` The Fugitive,'' which ran on <ORGANIZATION> ABC </ORGANIZATION> in 1963-67 and starred <PERSON> David </PERSON> <PERSON> Janssen </PERSON> as a man wrongly accused of killing his wife and was pursued by law enforcement authorities while searching for her killer. In `` The Immortal,'' on <ORGANIZATION> ABC </ORGANIZATION> during 1970-71, the lead character was a man immune to disease who was on the run because a ruthless billionaire wanted his special antibodies. The short-lived `` Hot Pursuit'' on <ORGANIZATION> NBC </ORGANIZATION> in 1984 focused on a young couple fleeing a false charge of murder, and a space alien and his son were chased by government scientists in <ORGANIZATION> ABC </ORGANIZATION>'s `` Starman'' in 1986-87. The form even inspired a CBS sitcom parody in 1966-67, `` Run Buddy Run,'' in which a hapless man was on the run from gangsters. In `` The Gifted One,'' as in `` The Fugitive,'' the hero is on a quest of his own while being pursued. He's looking for his real mother after learning he is not the son of the couple who raised him; he's running from the people who want to exploit his powers. `` The Gifted One'' is not as mystical as `` <PERSON> Kung </PERSON> <PERSON> Fu </PERSON>,'' about a Eurasian monk wandering the Old West while being pursued by agents of the <LOCATION> Chinese </LOCATION> imperial family and American bounty hunters. But, like `` <LOCATION> Kung </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Fu </LOCATION>,'' `` The Gifted One'' features flashbacks to the hero's childhood. The movie was to have been the pilot for a possible series, but the show is not on <ORGANIZATION> NBC </ORGANIZATION>'s fall schedule. `` I thought we'd get picked up for a series right away,'' <PERSON> Kowanko </PERSON> said. `` I still think we have a chance for a backup order. I think it's a good alternative. It's not a cop show. It's a fantasy. He has powers but he's not a super human being. He's not a space alien.'' <PERSON> Kowanko </PERSON>'s own background sounds like the concept for a series about a man on the move. He was born in <LOCATION> Australia </LOCATION> but was raised in <LOCATION> California </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Minnesota </LOCATION> after his parents divorced. He returned to <LOCATION> Australia </LOCATION> at 15 to mine sapphires with his stepfather. He worked in construction, was a deck hand on a <LOCATION> Mississippi </LOCATION> <LOCATION> River </LOCATION> towboat, waited tables and was a ski bum in <LOCATION> Colorado </LOCATION> when he was `` discovered'' and asked to audition for a commercial. `` I was an adventurous soul,'' he said. `` I worked on the <LOCATION> Mississippi </LOCATION> <LOCATION> River </LOCATION> during my <PERSON> Huck </PERSON> <PERSON> Finn </PERSON> fantasy. I worked from <LOCATION> St. </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Paul </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Minn. </LOCATION>, to Ste. <PERSON> Genevieve </PERSON>, <LOCATION> Mo. </LOCATION>, all 27 locks and dams, pushing 15 barges. My job as deck hand was to take the barges apart because only half could go through the locks at a time.'' He went to <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION> in 1980 and was signed to a development deal by <ORGANIZATION> ABC </ORGANIZATION>. Later, he was in the <ORGANIZATION> NBC </ORGANIZATION> series `` For Love and Honor.'' He played <PERSON> Willie </PERSON> <PERSON> Wolf </PERSON> in the movie `` Patty,'' about the kidnaping of <PERSON> Patricia </PERSON> <PERSON> Hearst </PERSON> by the <ORGANIZATION> Symbionese </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Liberation </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Army </ORGANIZATION>. In the last five years he has moved back and forth between here and <LOCATION> Australia </LOCATION>, where he and his mother own a fruit farm and vineyard in the <LOCATION> Outback </LOCATION> along the Tropic of <LOCATION> Capricorn </LOCATION>.
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
 Elsewhere in television: KOJAK RETURNS _ <PERSON> Telly </PERSON> <PERSON> Savalas </PERSON> will revive his role as <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION> detective <PERSON> Theo </PERSON> <PERSON> Kojak </PERSON> on the <ORGANIZATION> ABC </ORGANIZATION> Saturday Night Mystery Movie. `` Kojak'' was on <ORGANIZATION> CBS </ORGANIZATION> during 1973-78. <ORGANIZATION> ABC </ORGANIZATION> also is adding a segment starring <PERSON> Jaclyn </PERSON> <PERSON> Smith </PERSON> as `` <PERSON> Amanda </PERSON> <PERSON> Vanderbilt </PERSON>,'' a financial adviser to the wealthy. <PERSON> Peter </PERSON> <PERSON> Falk </PERSON> as `` Columbo'' and <PERSON> Burt </PERSON> <PERSON> Reynolds </PERSON> as `` B.J. Stryker'' will return to the `` Mystery Movie,'' but <ORGANIZATION> ABC </ORGANIZATION> has dropped the `` <PERSON> Gideon </PERSON> <PERSON> Oliver </PERSON>'' segment starring <PERSON> Louis </PERSON> <PERSON> Gossett </PERSON> <PERSON> Jr </PERSON>.
