<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <ORGANIZATION> LIN </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Broadcasting </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION> has rejected as inadequate a $ 5.85 billion takeover bid from <ORGANIZATION> McCaw </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Cellular </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Communications </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION> and said it was exploring alternatives. <PERSON> Lin </PERSON>, which has interests in cellular telephones, television and publishing, said its alternatives include staying independent, recapitalizing or selling itself to other potential buyers. <ORGANIZATION> McCaw </ORGANIZATION> has offered $ 120 a share for all of <ORGANIZATION> LIN </ORGANIZATION>'s shares. It said it was disappointed that the board had not accepted the offer, but added it was willing to discuss it with <ORGANIZATION> LIN </ORGANIZATION> executives.
