RGANIZATION> ABC </ORGANIZATION> special. He said <ORGANIZATION> KOA </ORGANIZATION> expects to fill its ad time on the special with previously-purchased advertising commitments. The show is the first in what <ORGANIZATION> ABC </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Radio </ORGANIZATION> says will be a series of <ORGANIZATION> American </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Agenda </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Radio </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Specials </ORGANIZATION> hosted by <ORGANIZATION> ABC </ORGANIZATION>'s top TV news figures, including <ORGANIZATION> ABC </ORGANIZATION> anchorman <PERSON> Peter </PERSON> <PERSON> Jennings </PERSON> and newsman <PERSON> Ted </PERSON> <PERSON> Koppel </PERSON>. `` I'm certain that as we continue this series that it will get wider acceptance,'' <PERSON> Giordano </PERSON> said. The next program is tentatively set for August and will deal with juvenile crime.
