 <PERSON> Alfred </PERSON> <PERSON> Checchi </PERSON>, who expects to meet this week with <ORGANIZATION> Transportation </ORGANIZATION> Secretary <PERSON> Samuel </PERSON> <PERSON> Skinner </PERSON> about his proposed $ 4 billion acquisition of <ORGANIZATION> Northwest </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Airlines </ORGANIZATION>, says fears about debt in the deal are `` almost laughable.'' `` The amount of debt in this proposal is not the least bit excessive,'' <PERSON> Checchi </PERSON> said Tuesday. `` The hardest part of my day was turning down all the banks that want to be part of this credit.'' <PERSON> Checchi </PERSON>'s investment group, <ORGANIZATION> Wings </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Holdings </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION>, signed a deal Monday to acquire <ORGANIZATION> Northwest </ORGANIZATION> parent <ORGANIZATION> NWA </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION> for $ 121 a share in cash. The financing includes $ 700 million in equity and $ 3.35 billion borrowed from a syndicate of commercial banks. <PERSON> Skinner </PERSON> wrote a letter May 15 to <ORGANIZATION> NWA </ORGANIZATION> Chairman <PERSON> Steven </PERSON> <PERSON> Rothmeier </PERSON> saying the department was concerned about any acquisition that would have a `` substantial adverse impact'' on the company's financial structure. <PERSON> Checchi </PERSON> said he expects to meet with <PERSON> Skinner </PERSON> today or Thursday in <LOCATION> Washington </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> D.C. </LOCATION> To complete a transaction by the Sept. 18 deadline imposed by <ORGANIZATION> NWA </ORGANIZATION>, <ORGANIZATION> Wings </ORGANIZATION> needs a license from the <ORGANIZATION> Transportation </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Department </ORGANIZATION>, which will examine the financial package to determine whether the group is financially fit to safely operate the nation's fourth-largest airline. Similar reviews have ranged in length from two months for an extensive fitness check la