<HEAD>Lorenzo Greets New Pilots, Says He's Confident About Rebuilding Eastern</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By DAN SEWELL</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>MIAMI (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <ORGANIZATION> Texas </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Air </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION>. Chairman <PERSON> Frank </PERSON> <PERSON> Lorenzo </PERSON> spoke with confidence about <ORGANIZATION> Eastern </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Airlines </ORGANIZATION>' future as he personally assured new pilots of a deep commitment to see the carrier succeed, despite a crippling 3-month-old strike `` Every day that goes by, you see more and more realization of what we're doing,'' <PERSON> Lorenzo </PERSON> told reporters Tuesday following graduation ceremonies for a group of <ORGANIZATION> Eastern </ORGANIZATION> recruits. `` An airline can be rebuilt, particularly an airline like <ORGANIZATION> Eastern </ORGANIZATION>, because of the tremendous strengths and the tremendous assets that the company has. I've been very encouraged by what I've seen. While Eastern, a unit of <ORGANIZATION> Texas </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Air </ORGANIZATION>, is selling assets to reduce its debt, <PERSON> Lorenzo </PERSON> said the carrier is moving ahead with rebuilding and has begun discussions with aircraft manufacturers on buying new aircraft for the 1990s. <PERSON> Lorenzo </PERSON> said he thought the federal bankruptcy court overseeing <ORGANIZATION> Eastern </ORGANIZATION>'s reorganization will approve the airline's plan to rebuild at two-thirds its prestrike size. He called the plan `` very, very reasonable ... a much more practical solution'' than the unions' call for a new owner or the leanings of some creditors toward complete liquidation. `` You do have creditors who are frustrated and they'd like to get their money,'' <PERSON> Lorenzo </PERSON> said. `` We intend to make sure the company honors its contracts and provides the creditors what they're due.'' He called the union-backed buyout effort by <LOCATION> Chicago </LOCATION> commodities trader <PERSON> Joseph </PERSON> <PERSON> Ritchie </PERSON> `` a joke'' and said there were no legitimate buyers for Eastern as a whole. Eastern has `` been overwhelmed by the interest in most of these assets'' it's offering for sale, but he declined to discuss pending transactions. Earlier, <PERSON> Lorenzo </PERSON>, Eastern President <PERSON> Phil </PERSON> <PERSON> Bakes </PERSON> and other executives were all smiles as they handed out diplomas and congratulations to 18 <ORGANIZATION> Eastern </ORGANIZATION> pilot recruits who completed training. `` We are very, very committed to the success of <ORGANIZATION> Eastern </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Airlines </ORGANIZATION>,'' <PERSON> Lorenzo </PERSON> told them. Company spokesman <PERSON> Robin </PERSON> <PERSON> Matell </PERSON> said <ORGANIZATION> Eastern </ORGANIZATION> has graduated 108 new pilots since it began seeking recruits about a month after the strike began March 4. He said there were 259 pilots who crossed the picket lines, not including 17 more veteran pilots who have told the company in the past week that they wish to return to work. There are 527 recruits in training, he said. <PERSON> Matell </PERSON> said Eastern is well on track toward having enough pilots to carry out the airline's planned schedule expansion this summer. A spokesman for the <ORGANIZATION> Air </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Line </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Pilots </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Association </ORGANIZATION> disputed that claim. `` We're not contradicting the statement in itself,'' said the spokesman, who asked not to be identified. `` But by numbers and by their own information, they are going to be able to fly the first days of the schedule, but they're not going to be able to continue to fly it'' due to lack of pilots. Eastern also announced Tuesday it will lease an A-300 <ORGANIZATION> Airbus </ORGANIZATION> jet to <ORGANIZATION> VIASA </ORGANIZATION>, <ORGANIZATION> Venezuelan </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> International </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Airways </ORGANIZATION>, for $ 1.4 million over four months. `` It's consistent with our announced business plan to make $ 1.8 billion in assets transactions and use more than $ 900 million to pay down debt,'' <PERSON> Matell </PERSON> said. Eastern is about $ 2.5 billion in debt. Earlier this month, its Northeastern Shuttle service was handed over to <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION> developer <PERSON> Donald </PERSON> <PERSON> Trump </PERSON> for $ 365 million. Eastern filed for Chapter 11 bankruptcy reorganization five days after its pilots and flight attendants unions joined a <ORGANIZATION> Machinists </ORGANIZATION> union strike that crippled the airline. <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> Bankruptcy Judge <PERSON> Burton </PERSON> <PERSON> R. </PERSON> <PERSON> Lifland </PERSON> in <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION> must approve any asset sales. He approved the shuttle deal and the $ 277.5 million sale last week of 15 planes and six aircraft engines to a company that buys and resells airplane equipment. Eastern last week announced a deal to sell eight <LOCATION> Philadelphia </LOCATION> airport gates, 16 jets and other assets to <ORGANIZATION> Midway </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Airlines </ORGANIZATION> for $ 206.5 million. <PERSON> Lifland </PERSON> must approve that transaction, and <ORGANIZATION> Eastern </ORGANIZATION> unions say they will challenge it.
