<HEAD>London Shares Higher At Midday</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Stock prices moved higher Wednesday as the market seemed unperturbed by the fall of the pound and a nationwide transportation strike. Volume was low as today's national rail strike, combined with a walkout by subway and bus drivers in <LOCATION> London </LOCATION>, left many brokerages and institutions understaffed. Much of the trading volume was in the pharmaceutical and electronics sectors, dealers said. The Financial Times-Stock Exchange 100 index was up 11.6 points, or 0.5 percent, at 2,176.4 at midday. Volume was a scant 176.1 million shares. The pound was quoted at $ 1.5345 and 3.0514 West German marks around midday Wednesday, down from $ 1.5475 and 3.0632 marks late Tuesday in <LOCATION> London </LOCATION>.
