<TEXT>
 <ORGANIZATION> RJR </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Nabisco </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION> said today it will sell its <ORGANIZATION> Chun </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> King </ORGANIZATION> food division for $ 52 million to a group of investors from <LOCATION> Singapore </LOCATION>. The sale is part of <PERSON> Nabisco </PERSON>'s continuing effort to reduce debt from its $ 24.5 billion buyout by <ORGANIZATION> Kohlberg </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Kravis </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Roberts </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION>; Co.. <ORGANIZATION> RJR </ORGANIZATION> Chairman <PERSON> Louis </PERSON> <PERSON> V. </PERSON> <PERSON> Gerstner </PERSON> <PERSON> Jr. </PERSON> said the agreement was reached with <PERSON> Yeo </PERSON> <PERSON> Hiap </PERSON> Seng Limited and <ORGANIZATION> Fullerton </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Holdings </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Pte </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Ltd. </ORGANIZATION>, a subsidiary of <ORGANIZATION> Temasek </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Holdings </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Pte </ORGANIZATION>. Ltd. The consumer products giant agreed to sell the <ORGANIZATION> Chun </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> King </ORGANIZATION> trademark, under which its line of shelf-stable Oriental food products is marketed, as well as sauce manufacturing equipment in <LOCATION> St. </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Theresa </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Canada </LOCATION>, and production facilities in <LOCATION> Cambridge </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Md. </LOCATION>, and <LOCATION> Ontario </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Canada </LOCATION>. The sale is pending approval of the <ORGANIZATION> Federal </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Trade </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Commission </ORGANIZATION>. RJR sold the Chun King frozen food line to <ORGANIZATION> ConAgra </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION> in 1986. Earlier this month, French food and beverage giant <ORGANIZATION> BSN </ORGANIZA